      • getAccessDeniedUntil

        public Date getAccessDeniedUntil()
        Description copied from interface: AccessResult
        If AccessResult.isAccessGranted() returns false, this method returns the Date until the access to the resource is denied, otherwise null. But it may return null, too, when the FailedAccessCounter doesn't provide such a date. This depends on the implementation (FailedAccessCounterImpl supports it).
        Specified by:
